<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-11-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-11-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="108" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d108">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hutchinson</persName> to
                                Mr. <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Santiago</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-11-08"><hi rend="italic">November 8,
                                1902</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Hutchinson reports that the money paid for cleaning the U. S. S. <hi rend="italic">Iowa</hi> has been returned by the Chilean Government,
                            that it is advisable to accept same, and requests immediate instructions
                            in the premises.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>